import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['cx'], data['cy'])
    plt.xlabel('cx')
    plt.ylabel('cy')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What is the distribution of cx and cy?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    name_counts = data['name'].value_counts()
    name_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.xlabel('Names')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the most common name in the dataset?')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    plt.scatter(data['cx'], data['cy'])
    
    m, b = np.polyfit(data['cx'], data['cy'], 1)
    plt.plot(data['cx'], m * data['cx'] + b, color='red', label=f'y = {m:.2f}x + {b:.2f}')
    
    plt.xlabel('cx')
    plt.ylabel('cy')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('What is the correlation between cx and cy?')
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
